com.opera.core.systems.internal

Class CallbackWait

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opera.core.systems.internal.CallbackWait
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ImplicitWait

    public abstract class CallbackWait
extends Object
    A variation of Selenium's Wait that uses Callable and that may have its timeout and polling interval configured on the fly. Each CallbackWait instance defines the maximum amount of time to wait for a condition, as well as the frequency with which to check the condition. Furthermore, the user may configure the wait to ignore specific types of exceptions whilst waiting, such as NoSuchElementException when searching for an element on the page.

        public <X> X until(Callable<X> condition)
